1) Read the input from the input file (inp.txt).
2) Find Unique modules by doing breadth-first-search every nodes of the tree and eliminating duplicates.
3) Print out all the unique modules and number of unique modules.
4) Find paths from transaction to defective module.
5) For this purpose use queue to implement breadth-first-search.
6) List all the paths
7) Check if the item reaches to defective module even if it is in visited nodes.
8) Print out the explosion of the system.
9) From each transaction do an extensive depth-first-search.
10) Use stack for this purpose.
11) Print out your explosion using required spaces.
12) If modules repeated add * with it. 